title: For Sale:  Scams are flooding Armslist
postcontent:
Scams are hitting this page left and right. I went through and pegged about 80% of the guns listed as scams. Here are some helpful pointers to identifying them;

They often come 2 or 3 at a time. 
Their pictures and descriptions are pulled straight from other gun sites like gunbroker.com. Do a google search of their description and you will see.
 Check the "listings by this user", there are often other guns of similar value all for sale, some of them are for sale in other states.
They are trying to sell guns that are now banned in MD
The gun is displayed really well with good lighting and photos look like it was taken with something better than an iPhone. Dealers on auction sites often have a red or white display table/cloth they take photos on to accent the guns features. Most real sellers typically put their gun on the floor and you can see their feet in the photo.
Their location is maryland, maryland or baltimore, baltimore, maryland
The gun is selling well under its value
If you email them, ask for something specific to the gun and to provide more photos. Also they will often drag on a few emails before asking you to wire money. NEVER WIRE MONEY.

Please flag any scammers you see out there. Lets take back our website.

title: For Sale:  Browning X-Bolt White Gold Medallion 280 Rem **NEW**
postcontent:
NIB Browning X-Bold White Gold Medallion in .280 Remington.



Receiver - Stainless steel • Polished finish • Glass bedded • Drilled and tapped for scope mounts • Scroll engraving on front and rear receiver

Barrel - 22 inch stainless steel • Polished stainless finish • Free-floating • Hand chambered • Target Crown

Action - Bolt-action • 60° bolt lift • Adjustable Feather Trigger™ • Detachable 4 round rotary magazine • Top-tang safety • Bolt Unlock Button

Stock - Gloss finish checkered walnut stock • Rosewood fore-end grip and pistol grip cap

Features - Sling swivel studs installed • Inflex Technology recoil pad



Browning has over 50 years of experience with bolt-action high-powered rifles. Today's X-Bolt rifle inherits the strongest, most note-worthy features of its predecessors. The X-Bolt White Gold model has a Monte Carlo stock. This feature is recognized as the comb steps sharply down toward the heel of the buttstock, allowing more contact between the recoil pad of the stock and the shooter's shoulder. With this design, the recoil of the fired shell comes directly back or in-line with the stronger part of the inner shoulder, making the rifle more pleasant to shoot, especially when a long day at the range is expected.

The X-Bolt White Gold is beautifully adorned with a polished stainless steel receiver that is drilled and tapped for scope mounts with engravings both the front and rear. This rifle also has a polished stainless steel barrel. Its stock is a gloss-finished, finely checkered with a rosewood forend and grip cap.

The White Gold's beauty is really on the inside, in how it shoots and what makes it so accurate. The three-lever Feather Trigger™ system is probably the most comfortable, simple trigger on any bolt-action rifle on the market. There is no take-up or creep and very little over-travel. This is the kind of trigger serious hunters and shooters demand. Next is the superb free-floating barrel with Target Crown, then triple-checked for interior finish, straightness and air-guaged for total uniformity. No doubt, this rifle has it all. Looks, handling and most important, dead-on accuracy.

title: For Sale:  Glock 19 (gen2) with optional Crimson Trace Laser
postcontent:
I'm selling a 2nd generation, two-letter S/N indicating this is an early production Glock 19. I bought this as a safe queen and collectable as I was looking for one that was basically brand-new. This one is in great shape, has no carry wear and the frame is in almost-mint condition minus a small scuff on the nose. Everything is matching and original, up to and including the pre-upgrade black parts that Glock used in the early 1990's.

The reason I am selling it is because the slide lock notch has been worked on. Meaning, the notch that the slide lock lever locks into to lock the slide back has been filed to actuate an easier release if you use the slide lock lever to drop the slide. It is a small alteration, and does not impede function, however it is a modification that I didn't want as I literally wanted a 100% original, unaltered gen2 G19 for collecting purposes. See picture below.

I am looking for $600. No mag included as I don't have any prebans or 10rounders. I also have a Crimson Trace lasergrip (# LG619) that I am looking to sell separately for $175 which is in likewise excellent condition. title: For Sale/Trade:  MUD RAILS - SIG 226 - 1986 - collector condition
postcontent:
have a 1986 Sig 226 with mud rail cutouts.  This was the last gen of the mudrails.  For those do not know about the mud rails sig in 1985-86 cut out slits in the frame rail so that the gun would shoot with sand, mud, or water in it.  

The Mud rails came under scrutiny when guys were having the frame rail crack when using 9mm+P ammo.  Alot of these guns were ruined by this.  My frame is in MINT condition with no wear marks at all.  I keep it oiled,  I keep it greased, and I am not an idiot and I use the right ammo.  I also added the EFK Dragon Frame Saver recoil system to prevent this ever happening to my gun.  I have the SIG E2 grips adde to this pistol as well.  



A Beautiful Tysons corner specimen.  They dont make them like this anymore.  Comes with 4 mags, a holster, and original grip parts.

SAKO Finnish (Nosin-Nagant) M-39 WW-ll Vintage Dated-1943 SA. (SA Finnish Army) All original parts w/matching numbers. This rifle is a collectors or shooters grade rifle. Stock is the original SAKO WW-II stock with no cracks or repairs. Bore has some War use, but is in good shooting condition. 
Note: Use caution and research the gun, before buying. So-called unissued and recently imported rifles that may not be completely Finnish authentic M-39's
